<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="607" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[699,1295,1909,2336]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Winton" authorityYear="1896" box="[701,969,2028,2062]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="10" pageNumber="607" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ansorgei">Lophuromys ansorgei</taxonomicName>
belongs in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1190,1294,2028,2062]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="10" pageNumber="607" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sikapusi">sikapusi</taxonomicName>
species complex and was resurrected by W. N. Verheyen and colleagues in 2000 based on morphology. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="607" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6898519" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6898519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6898519/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="607" startId="10.[700,872,2185,2219]" targetBox="[85,676,1919,2333]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[699,1295,1909,2336]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[700,876,2185,2219]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">Distribution.</emphasis>
S Cameroon, S ofSanaga River, E through Congo Basin to Uganda and W Kenya.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="607" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[699,1295,1909,2336]" lastBlockId="10.[86,1292,2347,2770]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[700,937,2302,2336]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 100-165 mm, tail 49-91 mm, ear 10-20 mm, hindfoot 20-26 mm; weight 45-111 g. Dorsum is reddish brown, and venteris slightly brighter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
