<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="607" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="10.[86,1292,2347,2770]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[88,442,2618,2652]" pageId="10" pageNumber="607">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Ansorge’s Brush-furred Rat was considered a synonym of the Western Brush-furred Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[982,1130,2658,2692]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="10" pageNumber="607" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sikapusi">L. sikapusi</taxonomicName>
), which was classified as Least Concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
